  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "OPERATIONS LEAD",
  "description": "<p>We are an established F&B business and are looking for an <strong>Operations Lead</strong> to support daily operations, strengthen operational standards, and work closely with management and outlet teams to ensure smooth day-to-day execution.</p><p>This is a hands-on role that requires a strong on-the-ground presence and flexibility to support business needs.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Suppor  and oversee daily outlet operations.</li><li>Ensure compliance with operational standards, SOPs, and service quality.</li><li>Conduct routine checks, follow-ups, and operational reviews.</li><li>Support outlet supervisors and staff with training and operational guidance.</li><li>Liaise with tenants, vendors, and staff where required.</li><li>Assist in implementing process improvements and standardisation.</li><li>Support new initiatives or concepts as the business evolves.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of prior experience in F&B or retail operations.</li><li>Able to communicate effectively in English and Mandarin to liaise with Chinese-speaking tenants and staff.</li><li>Hands-on, practical and detail-oriented.</li><li>Able  to work 6 days a week, including weekends and public holidays.</li><li>Able to work long hours based on operational requirements.</li><li>Familiar with SFA licence application and renewal process.</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Information</strong></p><ul><li>This  role is operational in nature and requires flexibility based on business  needs.</li><li>Scope may expand as new concepts or initiatives are introduced.</li></ul>",
